      "overflow": 926,
      "chipText": "→ not on its own -- a paused holder can act after expiry; you need a fencing token the resource enforces\nA lock is a performance optimization; correctness comes from the resource fencing on a monotonic token, or from a design that needs no exclusion -- and correctness-vs-efficiency decides which lock you even need.",
